Class LongRegion

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--pl.edu.agh.icsr.janet.util.LongRegion
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Cloneable, Region, java.io.Serializable
public final class LongRegion
extends java.lang.Object
implements Region

Represents a contiguous region in an array of longs. The region may be empty, or it may refer to the whole array. The original array is referenced rather than copied; changes made to it are immediately visible to region objects. This class may be used for passing "pointers into the middle of arrays" to native methods.
